irrigate /ˈɪrɪˌɡeɪt/

(irrigating,irrigated,irrigates) 

1. V-T To irrigate land means to supply it with water in order to help crops grow. 灌溉 

例： None of the water from Lake Powell is used to irrigate the area. 鲍威尔湖的水没有被用来灌溉这一地区。 

2. irrigation N-UNCOUNT 灌溉 

例： The agricultural land is hilly and the irrigation poor. 这片农田多丘陵，而且灌溉条件很差。

